reviews.text: MoM is a hidden gem the menu is basic and it is cheap but the food is great. The restaurant itself is very basic and with no natural light but it's perfect for lunch with no frills and quick. You need to go down a set of stairs from the ground level and it's down a corridor not very easy to find but worth the look.
Nice sounding system. Quite surprised for a local LiveHouse.

The sound balance is so bad that at one point I thought my ears were bleeding. Everything was too damn loud, high frequency were slicing through my ear drums. Audience were literally covering their ears and leaving because of that. It's a bad experience for both performers and audience.
Small Space for great gigs.
Great place for live music. Our music school rents this place for our end of term performance, it's just perfect
